name: Warung Makan MM
address: V979+QHX, Jl. Raya Singaraja - Amlapura, Les, Kec. Tejakula, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81173, Indonesia
review 1:
We randomly pulled up to this place and was invited in by the smiling lady.
As vegans we don't usually find local warung food that exciting (outside of touristy areas) but this one was full of flavour and not skimpy with vegetables and tempeh.
Wonderful service and It is super cheap too.
review 2: Excellent service and really great prices. The food might not knock your socks off, but you'll still leave with a full and happy belly.

name: La Kubu Homestay
address: Jl. Segara Sungu, Les, Kec. Tejakula, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81173, Indonesia
review 1: Nice and relaxed place to stay. Close to a local fishermen community. Not to many tourists. Stoney beach but you can snorkel at a local reef. Local farmers produce salt in the area which is interesting to observe. You can hear animals and some music from the village. Staff is very nice and helpful. Not easy to get in and out, so plan your transportation ahead.
review 2: Feels like home. Great place to stay when you visit Les, Tejakula. The owner is very friendly too! Pasti kembali lagi :)
review 3: Three separate rooms for good privacy. Close to the ocean - walk over early to see an amazing sunrise.
review 4: If you have any business in Les and want to be with the locals then this is your place.
